WEBVTT

00:01.435 --> 00:03.668
♪ Da, da, da-ba-da, da, da,
ba-da-ba-da-ba ♪

00:03.703 --> 00:05.170
♪ Da, da, da-ba-da, da, da ♪
Let's go!

00:05.205 --> 00:06.872
♪ We'll be there ♪

00:06.907 --> 00:09.541
♪ A wink and a smile
and a great old time ♪

00:09.576 --> 00:11.743
♪ Yeah, we'll be there ♪

00:11.778 --> 00:13.845
♪ Wherever we are,
there's some fun to be found ♪

00:13.880 --> 00:16.181
♪ We'll be there
when you turn that corner ♪

00:16.216 --> 00:17.516
♪ We'll jump out the bush ♪

00:17.551 --> 00:19.217
♪ With a big bear hug
and a smile ♪

00:19.252 --> 00:20.853
♪ We'll be there ♪

00:28.128 --> 00:29.828
Man: Earth.

00:29.863 --> 00:35.267
Not just our home, but home to
a number of different species.

00:35.302 --> 00:38.036
Some big...

00:38.071 --> 00:40.205
some small.

00:42.609 --> 00:48.013
And some that are so unique
they deserve a whole episode.

00:48.048 --> 00:50.949
Welcome to "Planet Bears,"

00:50.984 --> 00:55.454
hosted by yours truly,
Sir Lawrence Greyborough.

00:58.125 --> 00:59.691
In the quiet den,

00:59.726 --> 01:02.627
the bears are slowly
and peacefully awakened

01:02.662 --> 01:06.031
by the warmth
and sounds of spring.

01:06.066 --> 01:09.434
[ Alarm blaring ]

01:09.469 --> 01:12.537
Known to spend a third
of the day resting,

01:12.572 --> 01:16.608
the gentle and elusive panda
is slow to rise.

01:16.643 --> 01:20.712
The mighty grizzly begins
his day full of vigor.

01:20.747 --> 01:23.615
Good morning, world!
Good morning, room!

01:23.650 --> 01:26.318
Good morning,
motivational poster!

01:28.255 --> 01:30.122
Wakey, wakey, bro.

01:30.157 --> 01:31.890
Panda:
Five more minutes.

01:31.925 --> 01:34.326
Good morning, kitchen.
Good morning, trash can.

01:34.361 --> 01:36.094
How do you do,
microwave?

01:36.129 --> 01:37.896
Ah, so thirsty.

01:37.931 --> 01:40.265
Hmm, what can quench
my thirst today?

01:40.300 --> 01:41.900
Ooh, that'll work.

01:41.935 --> 01:44.736
Greyborough: While the grizzly
restores his electrolytes,

01:44.771 --> 01:48.473
the often silent and highly
skilled polar bear

01:48.508 --> 01:52.844
focuses on the most important
aspect of a bear's life.

01:52.879 --> 01:54.479
Uhh, need breakfast.

01:54.514 --> 01:56.281
Oh, yeah, you know what
would be awesome, Pan?

01:56.316 --> 01:57.482
French toast sticks.

01:57.517 --> 01:59.251
Ice bear needs
cooking space.

01:59.286 --> 02:01.486
Greyborough: The grizzly
and the panda

02:01.521 --> 02:03.522
wander off to distract
their minds

02:03.557 --> 02:06.191
from their rumbling tummies
so the polar bear

02:06.226 --> 02:08.961
can prepare their morning meal.

02:17.070 --> 02:21.373
<i>Man: Hello, and welcome to</i>
<i>the 41st annual Pug Bowl!</i>

02:21.408 --> 02:22.674
<i>[ Dog barks ]</i>

02:22.709 --> 02:24.376
Ah!
I forgot this was today!

02:24.411 --> 02:26.511
Yes!
- This game is gonna be so good!

02:26.546 --> 02:28.280
<i>We have some breaking news.</i>

02:28.315 --> 02:30.549
<i>It seems that the MVP</i>
<i>of the season, Rocket,</i>

02:30.584 --> 02:32.384
<i>will be missing out</i>
<i>on the game today</i>

02:32.419 --> 02:35.187
<i>due to a scratch</i>
<i>on his left paw.</i>

02:35.222 --> 02:36.388
Oh, what?!

02:36.423 --> 02:37.856
Boo! We want Rocket!

02:37.891 --> 02:39.391
Ice Bear looked
everywhere for food.

02:39.426 --> 02:40.859
Found nothing.

02:40.894 --> 02:43.695
Ugh! First Rocket gets hurt,
and now no breakfast?!

02:43.730 --> 02:45.564
Okay.
Okay, guys. Relax.

02:45.599 --> 02:47.832
No food?
There's only one place to go.

02:47.867 --> 02:49.801
Greyborough: The supermarket.

02:49.836 --> 02:53.538
This abundant food source
attracts every hungry species

02:53.573 --> 02:55.974
in the area,
which makes it crowded

02:56.009 --> 02:58.143
and therefore
highly competitive.

02:58.178 --> 02:59.911
[ Children screaming ]

02:59.946 --> 03:03.582
Ice Bear will get produce,
bread, granola bars.

03:03.617 --> 03:04.983
Panda, get cereal.

03:05.018 --> 03:06.918
Cereal?
- Ugh, that's so much pressure.

03:06.953 --> 03:08.720
I mean,
there's so many options.

03:08.755 --> 03:11.489
Which one is the right -- Oh,
hey, you dropped your cereal.

03:11.524 --> 03:13.925
Oh! [ Chuckles ]
Thank you so much!

03:13.960 --> 03:15.327
You're my hero!

03:15.362 --> 03:17.763
♪♪

03:19.532 --> 03:22.234
You know, I-I'll take care
of the cereal.

03:22.269 --> 03:23.668
[ Chuckles nervously ]

03:23.703 --> 03:25.870
I totally got this.
Ha, ha, ha.

03:25.905 --> 03:28.206
Ice bear needs carrots,
chicken, teriyaki sauce.

03:28.241 --> 03:32.043
You got it, but first I have
to respond to nature's call.

03:32.078 --> 03:34.112
That means I'm going
to the bathroom.

03:34.147 --> 03:35.914
Ice Bear got it.
- Cool.

03:35.949 --> 03:39.551
Greyborough: With the grizzly
needing to answer nature's call

03:39.586 --> 03:42.254
and the panda in search
of a potential mate,

03:42.289 --> 03:46.658
the young polar bear is left
to forage on his own.

03:48.495 --> 03:51.363
The limited supplies
at this fishing hole

03:51.398 --> 03:54.099
means competition will be great.

03:54.134 --> 03:58.170
Our polar bear will have
to wait his turn.

03:59.806 --> 04:01.539
Ohh, I got to go.
I got to go.

04:01.574 --> 04:02.774
Where are you, bathroom.

04:02.809 --> 04:04.075
Okay, so that's
three eggs and --

04:04.110 --> 04:06.044
Hi, I-I'm -- Do you know
where the bathroom is?

04:06.079 --> 04:07.145
I'm -- I'm sorry, honey.

04:07.180 --> 04:08.980
Can you -- Can you
tell me that again?

04:09.015 --> 04:10.949
-Um, can you help me?
<i>-Yo no se!</i>

04:10.984 --> 04:12.651
Uh,<i> gracias?</i>

04:12.686 --> 04:15.020
[ Chime rings ]
- Yes!

04:16.990 --> 04:19.858
Uh, am I supposed
to be back here?

04:22.028 --> 04:25.797
Greyborough: Having situated
himself near his potential mate,

04:25.832 --> 04:28.600
the panda hopes
to draw her attention.

04:28.635 --> 04:30.835
Hmm, Wheat Bars:
Breakfast on the Go.

04:30.870 --> 04:33.972
Well, that's perfect for me,
since I'm always on the go

04:34.007 --> 04:35.940
to, like,
the gym and stuff.

04:35.975 --> 04:37.809
Oh, totally!
- That's an excellent choice.

04:37.844 --> 04:40.145
You should also try the ones
with chocolate chips.

04:40.180 --> 04:42.247
Is that so?
Oh, do tell.

04:42.282 --> 04:43.581
Aah!
No, no, no, no, no!

04:43.616 --> 04:45.484
Watch out for the --

04:47.854 --> 04:48.820
[ Chuckles ]

04:48.855 --> 04:50.855
Clean up
on aisle five, right?

04:50.890 --> 04:52.624
[ Chuckles ]

04:52.659 --> 04:55.026
Greyborough:
Back at the fishing hole,

04:55.061 --> 04:57.629
our polar bear
finally gets his turn.

04:57.664 --> 04:58.963
How can I help you?

04:58.998 --> 05:00.699
Ice Bear would like
to purchase some salmon.

05:00.734 --> 05:01.966
I'm afraid
we're out of salmon.

05:02.001 --> 05:04.102
Tuna?
- We're out of tuna, too.

05:04.137 --> 05:05.637
Catfish, goldfish, cod?

05:05.672 --> 05:08.373
What do we still have?
Uh, let me think, uh...

05:08.408 --> 05:09.941
Yeah, we're out
of that, too.

05:09.976 --> 05:12.877
The hunt continues
for our hungry bear.

05:12.912 --> 05:16.147
Fortunately, he can settle
for the next-best thing.

05:16.182 --> 05:19.284
Competition, however,
is still at the forefront.

05:19.319 --> 05:22.687
Ah, you can cut
the passive-aggressiveness

05:22.722 --> 05:23.988
with a knife.

05:24.023 --> 05:26.124
The polar bear has been
challenged

05:26.159 --> 05:27.692
by an aggressive female

05:27.727 --> 05:31.363
and now must assert his
dominance in order to win

05:31.398 --> 05:35.400
his fish sticks or fight.

05:35.435 --> 05:37.235
Hi!

05:37.270 --> 05:40.638
Ah! Fish sticks!

05:40.673 --> 05:43.241
The polar bear will
have to continue

05:43.276 --> 05:45.176
his tireless search elsewhere,

05:45.211 --> 05:48.213
or settle for fried tofu.

05:48.248 --> 05:51.149
Ah, ah, ah, I need to go.

05:51.184 --> 05:52.884
Huh?

05:52.919 --> 05:56.254
[ Laughs ]
Oh, happy day!

05:56.289 --> 05:59.724
Greyborough: Bears are known for
their remarkable intelligence.

05:59.759 --> 06:02.761
They will often employ
several strategies

06:02.796 --> 06:04.929
to overcome an obstacle.

06:04.964 --> 06:07.132
[ Shouting ]

06:09.035 --> 06:10.769
[ Grunts ]

06:10.804 --> 06:12.971
Yah!
Ohh!

06:18.311 --> 06:20.111
[ Laughs ]

06:20.146 --> 06:21.446
[ Engine starts ]

06:21.481 --> 06:24.716
Greyborough: The grizzly's goal
is finally within reach,

06:24.751 --> 06:28.553
however, an enemy indigenous
to these parts

06:28.588 --> 06:30.855
is lurking in the shadows.
[ Whistling ]

06:30.890 --> 06:32.290
What -- Hey!
Get down from there!

06:32.325 --> 06:34.526
Uh, I'm sorry, sir.
- Just need to go to the bathroom.

06:34.561 --> 06:36.127
I'll turn it off.

06:36.162 --> 06:37.695
-Aah!
-Stop!

06:37.730 --> 06:40.532
[ Forklift beeping ]
Aaah! I'm trying!

06:40.567 --> 06:42.434
Help!

06:42.469 --> 06:44.302
[ Screaming ]

06:45.672 --> 06:47.773
[ Crashes ]

06:49.676 --> 06:52.644
[ Panting ]
- You are in big trouble, mister!

06:52.679 --> 06:54.779
Guess you won't have time
to go to the bathroom!

06:54.814 --> 06:58.583
It's okay. I don't think
I need to go anymore.

06:58.618 --> 07:00.318
Greyborough:
Humans and animals alike

07:00.353 --> 07:03.221
both have a parasympathetic
nervous system...

07:03.256 --> 07:04.556
Whoa, what the --

07:04.591 --> 07:08.660
...relaxing tensed muscles
in preparation for action.

07:08.695 --> 07:12.798
Shame -- a feeling
shared by all species.

07:16.369 --> 07:17.669
Respect.

07:17.704 --> 07:19.904
Let's find out
how the panda bear

07:19.939 --> 07:22.607
is doing in his quest for love.

07:22.642 --> 07:24.342
Hey, I'm really sorry
for knocking down

07:24.377 --> 07:26.244
the cereal pyramid.
I didn't mean to.

07:26.279 --> 07:28.279
Oh, don't worry about it.
Hey, listen,

07:28.314 --> 07:30.248
I'm the queen
of knocking stuff over.

07:30.283 --> 07:32.917
You should have seen the mess
I made with the soda pop tower.

07:32.952 --> 07:34.352
You think that's crazy?

07:34.387 --> 07:36.688
I once tried to inflate
a mattress here in the store,

07:36.723 --> 07:38.356
and I ended up
knocking over a shelf.

07:38.391 --> 07:41.159
Actually, based off
the security camera footage,

07:41.194 --> 07:45.230
<i>shelves,</i> in plural,
would be more accurate.

07:47.834 --> 07:50.034
Oh, what?!
You're the mattress man?!

07:50.069 --> 07:52.637
We've watched that security
footage so many times.

07:52.672 --> 07:54.138
What?!
You know about that?!

07:54.173 --> 07:56.374
Oh, my gosh,
this is so embarrassing.

07:56.409 --> 07:57.542
Are you kidding?

07:57.577 --> 07:59.210
You're, like,
a legend over here.

07:59.245 --> 08:00.979
Show me your ways, master.
[ Laughs ]

08:01.014 --> 08:02.881
Oh!
[ Chuckles ]

08:02.916 --> 08:05.216
So, um, could I maybe
get your number

08:05.251 --> 08:08.052
so that we could talk over
shelves together?

08:08.087 --> 08:09.888
[ Chuckles ]
Uh, yeah.

08:09.923 --> 08:11.723
That'd be fun.

08:11.758 --> 08:14.158
Hey, bro, so I think
we need to go, like, now.

08:14.193 --> 08:15.860
Ice Bear ready
to make meal now.

08:15.895 --> 08:17.562
Oh, I can check you guys
out over here.

08:17.597 --> 08:21.299
Greyborough: The bears have
collected an abundance of food,

08:21.334 --> 08:24.903
showing that they have a high
status among their peers.

08:24.938 --> 08:27.005
All right,
that'll be $60.

08:27.040 --> 08:29.441
Right-o.
Coming right up.

08:31.077 --> 08:33.745
Um, Ice Bear left
his wallet at home.

08:33.780 --> 08:35.079
[ Chuckles nervously ]

08:35.114 --> 08:36.915
Well,
do you have any money?

08:36.950 --> 08:39.250
Oh, that's right. [Chuckles]
I don't have any pockets.

08:39.285 --> 08:42.754
Um, how about an I.O.U.?
[ Chuckles ]

08:42.789 --> 08:45.990
Um, I don' think
that's a good idea.

08:46.025 --> 08:48.493
I can really get
in trouble for that.

08:48.528 --> 08:49.827
Um, please?

08:49.862 --> 08:51.596
Dude, do you want
to get me fired?

08:51.631 --> 08:53.565
I thought you were
different than that.

08:53.600 --> 08:54.832
Oh, no,
I didn't mean to --

08:54.867 --> 08:56.200
Is there a problem,
gentlemen?

08:56.235 --> 08:57.602
Wait a minute,
you again?!

08:57.637 --> 08:59.904
Whoa!
Let's get out of here, guys!

08:59.939 --> 09:01.272
Phew! That was close.

09:01.307 --> 09:03.775
I vote we never
come here again.

09:03.810 --> 09:06.611
But Ice Bear needs food
to make...food.

09:06.646 --> 09:08.880
Ugh, you're right.
Man, I'm hungry.

09:08.915 --> 09:11.349
[ Stomachs grumbling ]

09:11.384 --> 09:13.451
[ Birds squawking ]

09:13.486 --> 09:16.955
All right, bros, let's look
everywhere around the house.

09:16.990 --> 09:18.957
There has to be
some food somewhere.

09:18.992 --> 09:21.626
Greyborough: Desperate
for hunger salvation,

09:21.661 --> 09:24.496
the bears search for any small
morsel they can salvage.

09:26.933 --> 09:28.366
[ Gulps ]
Aah! Aah!

09:28.401 --> 09:30.969
Greyborough: The fact that
the bears haven't had

09:31.004 --> 09:33.838
anything to eat is truly
taking a toll on them.

09:37.510 --> 09:41.646
Finally, a grain of nourishment
is discovered.

09:41.681 --> 09:43.381
It's a simple equation.

09:43.416 --> 09:47.218
When hungry meets angry,
you get "hangry."

09:47.253 --> 09:49.087
[ All growling ]

09:52.425 --> 09:53.825
When it comes to hunger,

09:53.860 --> 09:57.228
bears have no loyalty
to family or friends.

09:57.263 --> 10:02.267
It is every bear for himself
until their hunger is satisfied.

10:04.771 --> 10:06.571
Aah!

10:06.606 --> 10:09.173
Greyborough: It's a fight
between power and aggression.

10:09.208 --> 10:12.343
The hungriest bear will be
the victorious one.

10:12.378 --> 10:14.646
[ Distorted growl ]

10:14.681 --> 10:18.016
<i>You're absolutely right, Chad,</i>
<i>this is an intense game.</i>

10:18.051 --> 10:20.685
<i>But wait a minute.</i>
<i>Whoa, whoa, this is amazing!</i>

10:20.720 --> 10:21.919
<i>I can't believe it!</i>

10:21.954 --> 10:23.788
<i>Rocket is coming off the bench,</i>

10:23.823 --> 10:25.456
<i>and he's wobbling</i>
<i>onto the field.</i>

10:25.491 --> 10:27.692
<i>How is he even gonna play</i>
<i>with a cast on, Chad?</i>

10:27.727 --> 10:29.927
<i>-I cannot believe my eyes!</i>
<i>-Go, Rocket! Go, Rocket!</i>

10:29.962 --> 10:31.129
<i>-Go, go, go!</i>
<i>-Is he gonna --</i>

10:31.164 --> 10:33.865
<i>-Go-o-o-o-o-al!</i>
<i>-Go-o-o-o-o-al!</i>

10:33.900 --> 10:35.500
<i>[ Laughs ]</i>

10:35.535 --> 10:39.037
<i>We are going into overtime,</i>
<i>ladies and gentlemen.</i>

10:39.072 --> 10:40.872
<i>Get yourself comfortable,</i>
<i>folks,</i>

10:40.907 --> 10:42.807
<i>'cause we gonna be here</i>
<i>for a long time.</i>

10:42.842 --> 10:44.375
[ All gulp ]

10:44.410 --> 10:45.476
[ All sigh ]

10:45.511 --> 10:47.679
Greyborough:
Even the scarcity of food

10:47.714 --> 10:50.715
cannot threaten the bond
connecting these three bears,

10:50.750 --> 10:53.284
who have proven that there
is nothing stronger

10:53.319 --> 10:56.054
than the love connecting family.

10:56.089 --> 10:59.858
Good night, Planet Bears.

11:04.163 --> 11:06.197
♪♪
